HEADWORD: Tureen
<hw>Tu*reen"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>terrine</ets>, L. <ets>terra</ets> earth. See
<er>Terrace</er>.]</ety> <def>A large, deep vessel for holding soup, or
other liquid food, at the table.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>terreen</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

